			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;

We currently copy the file into memory and out to disk before NaCl code can use it.  This touches every byte, and definitely pre-warms the buffer cache.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;

This slows down startup time, since we are limited by IPC overhead and, more importantly, disk latencies (on spinning media).

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;

Pepper provides a NaCl private interface for the plugin to get installed extension files as file descriptors, plus uniquely identifying metadata (needed for validation cache identity).

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;

Such an interface is available for use.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;[for users as well as other parts of the system]&lt;/b&gt;
